It is possible to coax that codegen out of clang. The trick is that you need the high half of the product, so you must use a larger type, in this case __uint128_t:<p><pre><code>    uint64_t div10(uint64_t y) {
        const uint64_t magic = 0xCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCDULL;
        __uint128_t prod = magic * (__uint128_t)y;
        return (uint64_t)(prod >> (64 + 3));
    }
</code></pre>
See <a href="http://libdivide.com" rel="nofollow">http://libdivide.com</a> for how to get this codegen with runtime constants (I am the author).
